      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the praline paste",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Toast the {{hazelnuts}} at 180°C fan for 10 minutes until golden. Rub off the skins in a cloth. Melt the {{caster-sugar}} (praline amount) in a dry saucepan over medium heat until deep amber. Stir in the hazelnuts and tip onto oiled baking paper. Leave to set hard. Break into pieces and blend in a food processor until it forms a smooth paste, this takes 3 to 5 minutes. Set aside.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake the choux ring",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 200°C fan. Melt the {{unsalted-butter}} (ring amount) with {{sea-salt-fine}} and 240 ml water. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat, beat in the {{plain-flour}} (ring amount) all at once, dry over heat for 1 minute. Cool 5 minutes. Beat in {{eggs}} (ring amount) gradually until the paste is glossy and falls in a slow ribbon. Draw a 22 cm circle on baking paper. Pipe two concentric choux rings on the circle, then a third ring on top of the join. Scatter with flaked {{blanched-almonds}}. Bake 35 to 40 minutes, deep gold. Pierce and dry for 5 minutes in the off oven. Cool completely.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the praline cream and fill",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the {{whole-milk}} to a simmer. Whisk the {{caster-sugar}} (cream amount) with the {{eggs}} (cream yolks) and {{plain-flour}} (cream amount). Pour the hot milk over while whisking, return to the pan, and cook over medium heat until thick and the flour is cooked out, about 3 minutes. Press baking paper against the surface and chill until cold. Beat the softened {{unsalted-butter}} (cream amount) until pale. Beat in the cold pastry cream a tablespoon at a time until smooth. Beat in the praline paste. Pipe generously into the split choux ring. Replace the lid, dust with {{icing-sugar}}, and chill for 1 hour before serving.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
